    <body>
        <desc>This piece is different from Banksy's normal artwork. 
            It isn't a painting or a statue. It is a life-size blow-up doll that has been 
            dressed in prisoner orange and handcuffed with a black hood placed over its face.
            The doll was placed next to the "Big Thunder Mountain Railroad" at Disneyland in 
            California. The piece refers to the war on terror and to highlight the plight of 
            terror suspects. </desc>
